ince|ja|肥後国|12=draft}} (referenced in "Kantō Chijōjō-an," Jōō 3, 21st day of the 5th month). Connected to the {{ill|Kino Clan|ja|紀氏|1=Kii no Kuni no Miyatsuko|de|Ki (Klan)|uk|Рід Кі|ko|기씨 (황별)|fr|Kii no Kuni no Miyatsuko|3=紀伊国造|12=draft}}, descendants of the priests of {{ill|Iwashimizu Hachimangū Shrine|ja|石清水八幡宮|12=draft}} in Kyoto. * {{ill|Ōno Clan (Hizen Province)|ja|大野氏 (肥前国)|12=draft}} - Originated from Ōno Manor in {{ill|Takagi District, Hizen Province|ja|高木郡|12=draft}}, {{ill|Hizen Province|ja|肥前国|12=draft}} (referenced in the "Fukae Family Documents," designated an Important Cultural Property of Saga Prefecture, March 16, 1987). * The '''Ōno Clan''' was also a surname of the {{ill|Xianbei|ja|鮮卑|12=draft}} or {{ill|Gaoche|ja|高車|12=draft}} peoples. It was granted to {{ill|Li Hu|ja|李虎|12=draft}} by Emperor {{ill|Xiaowen of Northern Wei|ja|北魏の孝文帝|12=draft}}.
