'''Ōno Clan''' (大野氏) refers to one of the Japanese clans. Apart from the lineage described below, many other clans share this name.

* The ancient aristocratic Ōno Clan was a branch of the {{ill|Kamitsukeno Clan|ja|上毛野氏|1=Kamitsukeno clan|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and bore the title {{ill|Ason|ja|朝臣|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
* {{ill|Ōno Clan (Musashi Province)|ja|大野氏 (武蔵国)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - Originated from Ōno Village, {{ill|Chichibu District, Musashi Province|ja|秩父郡|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Musashi Province|ja|武蔵国|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
* {{ill|Ōno Clan (Owari Province)|ja|大野氏 (尾張国)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - Originated from Ōno Village, {{ill|Chita District, Owari Province|ja|知多郡|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Owari Province|ja|尾張国|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. Descended from the Uno branch of the {{ill|Seiwa Genji|ja|清和源氏|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (also called the {{ill|Asahi Clan|ja|朝日氏|qq=draft|qq=draft}}).
* {{ill|Ōno Clan (Echizen Province)|ja|大野氏 (越前国)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - Originated from {{ill|Ōno District, Echizen Province|ja|大野郡 (福井県)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Echizen Province|ja|越前国|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. Similarly descended from the Shiba branch of the Seiwa Genji.
* {{ill|Ōno Clan (Harima Province)|ja|大野氏 (播磨国)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - Originated from Ōno in Hokujō Township, {{ill|Harima Province|ja|播磨国|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (currently Ōno, {{ill|Kakogawa, Hyōgo|ja|加古川市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Hyōgo Prefecture). Claimed descent from the {{ill|Uda Genji|ja|宇多源氏|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and produced figures such as {{ill|Bunkan|ja|文観|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, a monk serving Emperor {{ill|Go-Daigo|ja|後醍醐天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
