* {{ill|Ōno Clan (Bungo Province)|ja|大野氏 (豊後国)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - Originated from Ōno Township in {{ill|Ōno District, Bungo Province|ja|大野郡|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Bungo Province|ja|豊後国|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. A branch of the {{ill|Ōgami Clan (Bungo Province)|ja|大神氏 (豊後国)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
* {{ill|Ōno Clan (Higo Province)|ja|大野氏 (肥後国)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - Originated from Ōno Beppu in {{ill|Higo Province|ja|肥後国|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (referenced in "Kantō Chijōjō-an," Jōō 3, 21st day of the 5th month). Connected to the {{ill|Kino Clan|ja|紀氏|1=Kii no Kuni no Miyatsuko|de|Ki (Klan)|uk|Рід Кі|ko|기씨 (황별)|fr|Kii no Kuni no Miyatsuko|3=紀伊国造|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, descendants of the priests of {{ill|Iwashimizu Hachimangū Shrine|ja|石清水八幡宮|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in Kyoto.
* {{ill|Ōno Clan (Hizen Province)|ja|大野氏 (肥前国)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - Originated from Ōno Manor in {{ill|Takagi District, Hizen Province|ja|高木郡|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Hizen Province|ja|肥前国|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (referenced in the "Fukae Family Documents," designated an Important Cultural Property of Saga Prefecture, March 16, 1987).
* The '''Ōno Clan''' was also a surname of the {{ill|Xianbei|ja|鮮卑|qq=draft|qq=draft}} or {{ill|Gaoche|ja|高車|qq=draft|qq=draft}} peoples. It was granted to {{ill|Li Hu|ja|李虎|qq=draft|qq=draft}} by Emperor {{ill|Xiaowen of Northern Wei|ja|北魏の孝文帝|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.

