'''Ōno Clan''' (大野氏) refers to one of the Japanese clans. Apart from the lineage described below, many other clans share this name.
* The ancient aristocratic Ōno Clan was a branch of the {{ill|Kamitsukeno Clan|ja|上毛野氏|1=Kamitsukeno clan|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and bore the title {{ill|Ason|ja|朝臣|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. * {{ill|Ōno Clan (Musashi Province)|ja|大野氏 (武蔵国)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - Originated from Ōno Village, {{ill|Chichibu District, Musashi Province|ja|秩父郡|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Musashi Province|ja|武蔵国|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. * {{ill|Ōno Clan (Owari Province)|ja|大野氏 (尾張国)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - Originated from Ōno Village, {{ill|Chita District, Owari Province|ja|知多郡|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Owari Province|ja|尾張国|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. Descended from the Uno branch of the {{ill|Seiwa Genji|ja|清和源氏|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (also called the {{ill|Asahi Clan|ja|朝日氏|qq=draft|qq=draft}}). * {{ill|Ōno Clan (Echizen Province)|ja|大野氏 (越前国)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - Originated from {{ill|Ōno District, Echizen Province|ja|大野郡 (福井県)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Echizen Province|ja|越前国|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. Similarly descended from the Shiba branch of the Seiwa Genji. * {{ill|Ōno Clan (Harima Province)|ja|大野氏 (播磨国)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - Originated from Ōno in Hokujō Township, {{ill|Harima Province|ja|播磨国|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (currently Ōno, {{ill|Kakogawa, Hyōgo|ja|加古川市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Hyōgo Prefecture). Claimed descent from the {{ill|Uda Genji|ja|宇多源氏|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and produced figures such as {{ill|Bunkan|ja|文観|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, a monk serving Emperor {{ill|Go-Daigo|ja|後醍醐天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. * {{ill|Ōno Clan (Iyo Province)|ja|大野氏 (伊予国)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - Originated from Ōno in {{ill|Kita District, Iyo Province|ja|喜多郡|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Iyo Province|ja|伊予国|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. Claimed lineages include the {{ill|Tachibana Clan|ja|橘氏|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Fujiwara Clan, or descendants of Prince {{ill|Iyo|ja|伊予親王|1=Iyo Shinnō|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. * {{ill|Ōno Clan (Bungo Province)|ja|大野氏 (豊後国)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - Originated from Ōno Township in {{ill|Ōno District, Bungo Province|ja|大野郡|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Bungo Province|ja|豊後国|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. A branch of the {{ill|Ōgami Clan (Bungo Province)|ja|大神氏 (豊後国)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. * {{ill|Ōno Clan (Higo Province)|ja|大野氏 (肥後国)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - Originated from Ōno Beppu in {{ill|Higo Province|ja|肥後国|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (referenced in "Kantō Chijōjō-an," Jōō 3, 21st day of the 5th month). Connected to the {{ill|Kino Clan|ja|紀氏|1=Kii no Kuni no Miyatsuko|de|Ki (Klan)|uk|Рід Кі|ko|기씨 (황별)|fr|Kii no Kuni no Miyatsuko|3=紀伊国造|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, descendants of the priests of {{ill|Iwashimizu Hachimangū Shrine|ja|石清水八幡宮|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in Kyoto. * {{ill|Ōno Clan (Hizen Province)|ja|大野氏 (肥前国)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} - Originated from Ōno Manor in {{ill|Takagi District, Hizen Province|ja|高木郡|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Hizen Province|ja|肥前国|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (referenced in the "Fukae Family Documents," designated an Important Cultural Property of Saga Prefecture, March 16, 1987). * The '''Ōno Clan''' was also a surname of the {{ill|Xianbei|ja|鮮卑|qq=draft|qq=draft}} or {{ill|Gaoche|ja|高車|qq=draft|qq=draft}} peoples. It was granted to {{ill|Li Hu|ja|李虎|qq=draft|qq=draft}} by Emperor {{ill|Xiaowen of Northern Wei|ja|北魏の孝文帝|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
== See also == * {{ill|Ōno Castle|ja|大野城|qq=draft|qq=draft}}
