onnected to the {{ill|Kino Clan|ja|紀氏|1=Kii no Kuni no Miyatsuko|de|Ki (Klan)|uk|Рід Кі|ko|기씨 (황별)|fr|Kii no Kuni no Miyatsuko|3=紀伊国造|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kino Clan|13=User:Immanuelle/Kii no Kuni no Miyatsuko|qq=}}, descendants of the priests of {{ill|Iwashimizu Hachimangū Shrine|ja|石清水八幡宮|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Iwashimizu Hachimangū Shrine|qq=}} in Kyoto. * {{ill|Ōno Clan (Hizen Province)|ja|大野氏 (肥前国)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōno Clan (Hizen Province)|qq=}} - Originated from Ōno Manor in {{ill|Takagi District, Hizen Province|ja|高木郡|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takagi District, Hizen Province|qq=}}, {{ill|Hizen Province|ja|肥前国|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hizen Province|qq=}} (referenced in the "Fukae Family Documents," designated an Important Cultural Property of Saga Prefecture, March 16, 1987). * The '''Ōno Clan''' was also a surname of the {{ill|Xianbei|ja|鮮卑|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Xianbei|qq=}} or {{ill|Gaoche|ja|高車|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gaoche|qq=}} peoples. It was granted to {{ill|Li Hu|ja|李虎|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Li Hu|qq=}} by Emperor {{ill|Xiaowen of Northern Wei|ja|北魏の孝文帝|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Xiaowen of Northern Wei|qq=}}.
