Province]]. Claimed lineages include the [[:en:Tachibana clan (kuge)|Tachibana Clan]], Fujiwara Clan, or descendants of Prince {{ill|Iyo|ja|伊予親王|1=Iyo Shinnō|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Iyo|13=User:Immanuelle/Iyo Shinnō|qq=}}. * {{ill|Ōno Clan (Bungo Province)|ja|大野氏 (豊後国)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōno Clan (Bungo Province)|qq=}} - Originated from Ōno Township in [[:en:Ōno District, Gifu|Ōno District, Bungo Province]], [[:en:Bungo Province|Bungo Province]]. A branch of the {{ill|Ōgami Clan (Bungo Province)|ja|大神氏 (豊後国)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōgami Clan (Bungo Province)|qq=}}. * {{ill|Ōno Clan (Higo Province)|ja|大野氏 (肥後国)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōno Clan (Higo Province)|qq=}} - Originated from Ōno Beppu in [[:en:Higo Province|Higo Province]] (referenced in "Kantō Chijōjō-an," Jōō 3, 21st day of the 5th month). Connected to the {{ill|Kino Clan|ja|紀氏|1=Kii no Kuni no Miyatsuko|de|Ki (Klan)|uk|Рід Кі|ko|기씨 (황별)|fr|Kii no Kuni no Miyatsuko|3=紀伊国造|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kino Clan|13=User:Immanuelle/Kii no Kuni no Miyatsuko|qq=}}, descendants of the priests of [[:en:Iwashimizu Hachimangū|Iwashimizu Hachimangū Shrine]] in Kyoto. * {{ill|Ōno Clan (Hizen Province)|ja|大野氏 (肥前国)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōno Clan (Hizen Province)|qq=}} - Originated from Ōno Manor in {{ill|Takagi District, Hizen Province|ja|高木郡|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takagi District, Hizen Province|qq=}}, [[:en:Hizen Province|Hizen Province]] (referenced in the "Fukae Family Documents," designated an Important Cultural Property of Saga Prefecture, March 16, 1987). * The '''Ōno Clan''' was also a surname of the [[:en:Xianbei|Xianbei]] or [[:en:Kang-chü|Gaoche]] peoples. It was granted to [[:en:Li Hu (general)|Li Hu]] by Emperor {{ill|Xiaowen of Northern Wei|ja|北魏の孝文帝|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Xiaowen of Northern Wei|qq=}}.
== See also == * [[:en:Ōno Castle|Ōno Castle]]
